# Repo-root .dockerignore (sprint-16 P7).
#
# All worker images (services/workers/{sfincs,modflow,swmm}/Dockerfile) build
# with the REPO ROOT as the build context (see infra/aws-batch/RUNBOOK.md
# "Run from the repo root"). Each Dockerfile COPYs ONLY its own
# services/workers/<name>/ subtree, so everything below is safe to prune from
# the context for EVERY worker build — it shrinks the upload, speeds the build,
# and keeps secrets/state/caches out of any layer.
#
# CONSERVATIVE BY DESIGN: with one explicit, commented exception (the SWMM P0
# reference spike, below), this lists ONLY paths that NO worker Dockerfile COPYs
# into its image (verified against the sfincs/modflow/swmm Dockerfiles) — so the
# existing SFINCS + MODFLOW images stay byte-identical. It does NOT exclude
# docs/reports/*.md/fixtures, which the MODFLOW build COPYs as part of its
# services/workers/modflow/ subtree.

# Version control + IDE
.git
.gitignore
.github
.vscode
.idea

# Python build/test caches + venvs (the worker images build their OWN venv)
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.tox
**/*.egg-info
**/.venv
**/venv
.coverage
**/htmlcov

# Node / web build artifacts (the workers are pure Python — none of this is copied)
**/node_modules
services/web/dist
services/web/build
**/.next

# OpenTofu / Terraform state + plans (NEVER ship into an image)
**/.terraform
**/*.tfstate
**/*.tfstate.*
**/tfplan
**/*.tfplan

# Local env + secrets
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.local

# Local spike scratch output (not part of any worker build)
**/_spike_out

# SWMM P0 reference spike — kept in-repo (the urban-engine docstrings in
# swmm_hyetograph.py / swmm_mesh_builder.py cite its path as the source of every
# swmm-api signature), but it is a DEV reference, not runtime. The SWMM
# Dockerfile COPYs the whole services/workers/swmm/ subtree, so exclude this one
# file explicitly to keep the 26 KB script out of the shipped image (bare-bones
# hygiene norm). swmm-only; does not affect the SFINCS/MODFLOW images.
services/workers/swmm/spike_quasi2d.py

# SFINCS deck-builder worker — the Dockerfile COPYs the whole
# services/workers/sfincs_deckbuilder/ subtree; keep the dev-only test + README
# out of the shipped GPL image (bare-bones hygiene norm). sfincs_deckbuilder-only.
services/workers/sfincs_deckbuilder/test_entrypoint.py
services/workers/sfincs_deckbuilder/README.md

# OS cruft
**/.DS_Store
